===Noun===
'''counselor''' (''plural:'' '''counselors''') {{US}}
#A [[professional]] who [[counsel]]s people, especially on personal problems.
#In the field of [[Counseling]], a licensed and professionally trained counselor who provides [[counseling]] in many forms, including [[Community Counseling]], [[Rehabilitation Counseling]], [[Marriage and Family Counseling]], [[School Counseling]], [[Mental Health Counseling]], and [[College Counseling]].
# In the field of [[education]], a [[School Counselor]]  on a special subject such as [[careers]], [[education]], or [[health]]
# In the field of [[law]], a counselor, counsellor, counselor-at-law or counsellor-at-law is an [[attorney]]
# In the field of [[politics]], a high ranking [[diplomat]], usually just below an [[ambassador]] or [[minister]]
# In the field of [[leisure]], a children's [[supervisor]], usually at [[camp]]

